    dc:creator "Wood, Kenneth R.; Wagner, Warren L." ;
    dc:date "2017" ;
    dc:title "Athyrium haleakalae (Athyriaceae), a new rheophytic fern species from East Maui, Hawaiian Islands: with notes on its distribution, ecology, and conservation status" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/phytokeys.76.11637.figure1>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/phytokeys.76.11637.figure4>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/phytokeys.76.11637.figure2>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/phytokeys.76.11637.figure3> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/phytokeys.76.11637.figure1>
    dc:description "Figure 1. Athyrium haleakalae K. R. Wood & W. L. Wagner. A-B habit C detail of adaxial pinnule showing venation and fleshy spines D detail of abaxial pinnule showing range of sori shapes E-F lower stipe scales G rhizome scale. A-G from Perlman et al. 23964 (BISH, PTBG, UC, US) (Illustration by Alice Tangerini)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/118766" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/phytokeys.76.11637.figure4>
    dc:description "Figure 4. A Mature plants of Athyrium haleakalae, showing habitat preference along concave hollow of stream, Hana Forest Reserve, East Maui, HI (22 Aug 2013, Wood & Oppenheimer 15639) B Mature plant of Athyrium microphyllum, showing terrestrial habitat preference, erect rhizome, and large size, Mohihi, Kaua'i, HI (18 Dec 2014, Wood & Flynn et al. 16175). Photos by K. R. Wood." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/118769" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/phytokeys.76.11637.figure2>
    dc:description "Figure 2. Map showing known distribution of Athyrium haleakalae, East Maui, HI, with upper right red dot indicating colonies in the headwaters of Kawakoe and Mokulehua, upper left in Helele'ike'oha, and lower red in Kīpahulu, near Palikea." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/118767" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/phytokeys.76.11637.figure3>
    dc:description "Figure 3. Typical habitat of Athyrium haleakalae around stream plunge pools, Hana Forest Reserve, East Maui, HI. Photo by K. R. Wood, 21 Aug 2013." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/118768" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

